{"questionId":"22582920","questionHtml":"<p>Write down matrices <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi></math> is a diagonal matrix.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nb